REPLACE INTO multilingual(`key`,language,value,guid) values("abstract","en","Human lactoferrin (hLF) is a member of non-specific immune system, it plays many roles, such as resistances against bacteria, fungi and viruses, etc. In this paper, hLF cDNA directed by the tuber specific promoter of class I patatin gene of potato (Solanum tuberosum L.) were transferred into potato mediated by Agrobacterium tumefiens transformation. hLF transgenic potato plants were confirmed by PCR detection, further RT-PCR showed that hLF RNAs were expressed in transgenic plants. hLF activities were detected by ELISA and Western blot analysis in hLF transgenic potato tubers.","10.3969/j.issn.1005-3395.2008.05.006");
